    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix NULL message handling in RRC NR UE task\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrc_nrue()` function in the NR UE RRC stack does not properly handle cases where `itti_receive_msg()` returns NULL. This can occur when the ITTI task has multiple file descriptors registered and receives events on non-message file descriptors.\n\nWhen this happens, the function attempts to dereference a NULL pointer when accessing message fields, leading to a segmentation fault.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_UE.c`: Added NULL check after `itti_receive_msg()` call and before message processing. Also added NULL check before calling `itti_free()`.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure NR UE with multiple ITTI file descriptors\n2. Send events to non-message file descriptors registered with the RRC NR UE task\n3. Observe segmentation fault when `rrc_nrue()` attempts to process the NULL message\n\nThe fix ensures that when `itti_receive_msg()` returns NULL, the function returns early without attempting to process message fields, preventing the crash.\n"
}